---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ContentFooter from '../components/ContentFooter.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <syn-card>
    <h1 class="syn-heading--2x-large" slot="header">
      Frequently misunderstood topics
    </h1>

    <p>
      This page clarifies common misconceptions about the Synergy Design System.
      It helps distinguish between what Synergy provides, what it enables,
      and what is intentionally left to applications and teams.
    </p>

    <p>
      This page is <strong>non-normative</strong> and does not define component
      behavior or API contracts.
    </p>

    <h2 class="syn-heading--large">Common misconceptions</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong><quote>"Synergy provides complete application layouts."</quote></strong><br>
        Synergy provides components and composition patterns,
        but does not define full page layouts or application structure.
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong><quote>"Using Synergy automatically guarantees accessibility."</quote></strong><br>
        Components are built with accessibility in mind,
        but correct usage and application context remain essential.
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong><quote>"Examples introduce additional supported features."</quote></strong><br>
        Examples demonstrate usage of documented APIs only
        and do not add new capabilities.
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong><quote>"If it exists in Storybook, it is part of the specification."</quote></strong><br>
        Storybook shows implementation examples.
        The specification is defined on this documentation site.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <ContentFooter
      creationDate={new Date().toISOString()}
      entityId={null}
    >
      | Normative component behavior and API contracts are defined on individual component pages.
    </ContentFooter>
  </syn-card>
</Layout>
